added.description: Francine is frustrated that Stan only pretends to pay attention when she talks.  Stan takes a pill engineered by the C.I.A. to help male agents listen to females.  Stan takes too much and the pill physically transforms him into a woman.
added.title: Stan Goes On The Pill

added.description: The villains, Emory and Oglethorpe, kidnap Master Shake and replace him with a "replicant" alien. However, Frylock and Meatwad soon realize the truth because the "replicant" doesn't really look like Shake.
added.title: Bad Replicant

added.description: Master Shake traps Meatwad in the clothes dryer for a week, accidentally giving him super powers. Meatwad ends up creating a balloon monster with his new electro-static power.
added.title: Balloonenstein

added.description: Master Shake becomes convinced that a vampire bus is waiting for him outside. So, the Aqua Teens go to Memphis on a fact-finding mission.
added.title: Bus of the Undead
tags: aqua teen hunger force athf episode 3 bus of the undead jon benjamin moth monster man vampire dracula grave

added.description: Master Shake sells Meatwad to the circus, only to become jealous when Meatwad becomes a huge success. Shake tries to become a circus performer too, but no one likes him.
added.title: Circus

added.description: Meatwad becomes depressed because his brain is really a squeak toy. Frylock gives him a new super-brain, turning Meatwad into an arrogant jerk.
added.title: Dumber Days

added.description: Meatwad gets a new doll, Happy Time Harry, which has a really bitter and jaded personality.  Happy Time Harry's negativity begins to affect all of the Aqua Teens.
added.title: Dumber Dolls

added.description: A gang of miscreant leprechauns takes out an ad on the Internet in an attempt to mug people for their shoes. The Aqua Teens ruin their plans when Master Shake finds them in the woods.
added.title: Escape from Leprechaupolis
tags: aqua teen hunger force athf episode 2 escape from leprechaupolis leprechauns rainbow gold machine woods

added.description: While surfing the Internet, Master Shake and Meatwad accidentally infect the house with obtrusive pop-up windows.
added.title: Interfection

added.description: Frylock discovers a mummy in the crawlspace under the Aqua Teens' house. The mummy begins to extort favors from Frylock with the threat of an ancient Egyptian curse.
added.title: Love Mummy
tags: ATHF Aqua Teen Hunger Force Episode 12 Mummy

added.description: Meatwad and Carl become addicted to rap music and candy after they begin listening to the new album from MC Pee Pants.
added.title: MC Pee Pants
tags: aqua teen hunger force athf episode 9 mc pee pants chris candy spider

added.description: Master Shake and Carl Split the cost of bringing a mail order bride over from Russia whom they both plan to marry.
added.title: Mail Order Bride

added.description: Master Shake rents out Meatwad's room to moon people. They end up being a bad influence on Meatwad. Frylock blasts them with his eye beams until they flee the planet.
added.title: Mayhem of the Mooninites

added.description: Master Shake's filth creates a new life form, Ol' Drippy (who has excellent manners). Master Shake becomes jealous of Ol' Drippy's popularity and starts to behave obnoxiously.
added.title: Ol' Drippy

added.description: Master Shake loses his PDA and he's convinced that it has been stolen by a mysterious, unknown Tar Monster.
added.title: PDA

added.description: Dr. Weird invents a giant mechanical robot that destroys Carl's car.  The Aqua Teens head to the mall to see if they can solve the mystery.
added.title: Rabbot
tags: aqua teen hunger force athf episode 1 rabbot premiere first car hair mall robot

added.description: The Mooninites return with a belt that grants them the abilities of a 70's super group.  Using the belt's powers, they create all sorts of havoc... until Carl stops them.
added.title: Revenge of the Mooninites

added.description: Frylock meets two aliens with suspicious motives. Their stupidity bores Frylock, so he trades places with Master Shake. Meanwhile, Meatwad burns down Carl's house.
added.title: Space Conflict from Beyond Pluto

added.description: King Star King is back! And this time he's a fat, bald, middle-aged slob with a family, a mortgage and a job at Amazon. Join King Star King, Hank Waffles, Pooza, and Gerbils on a dimension spanning adventure to save King Star King's family!
added.title: KING STAR KING!/!/!/

added.description: An auction of rare items draws Lupin's notice, but he isn't the only one with eyes on the prize. Is this newcomer a formidable stranger, or are they connected to Lupin's past?
added.title: An Invitation From the Past

removed.description: Lupin's after a historic railway ticket in the possession of Duke Marquis. It'll take teamwork to bring home the prize, but a certain butler wants to get in the way.
removed.title: Adventure Along the (Bogus) Transcontinental Railroad

removed.description: Steve and Roger discover that the house is haunted.  The ghost appears as an apparition of a younger Francine.  The ghost grows more powerful until it attacks Hayley's boyfriend and pulls him into the netherworld.
removed.title: Poltergasm
